Description.Text: This hotel was voted best hotel in Russia 1999. 0308SC
The hotel is situated on the banks of the river moskva opposite the red square, the kremlin and st basil's cathedral. The nearest metro is about 20 minutes' walk away.

The very spacious rooms are very well equiped with all the facilities expected from a top international hotel. The decor is white and red with beige shades. Some rooms have a view over the moskva river and the cathedral of st basil and the kremlin.
The exterior is traditional, pale baroque.

The main restaurant is situated on the first floor again with fine views over st basil's cathedral and the kremlin. The restaurant is dominated by a sumptuous buffet. The fine dining, exclusive romanoff restaurant is located on the upper floors of the hotel. It is widely regarded as one of the finest dining experiences available in Moscow.

The medium sized lobby area is cosy with brown shades predominating. The area is very busy particularly for concluding business deals. The reception area is to the right on entering the hotel and the lobby bar is to the rear. The Vienna cafe and boutiques are just off the lobby to the left.
